{"title":"USA Cycling XC MTB National Series Returns for 2025","link":"https://bikerumor.com/usa-cycling-xc-mtb-national-series-returns-for-2025/","date":1739897955000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel.png\" width=\"1154\" height=\"634\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series big wheel\" /></p>\n<p>The USA Cycling Cross-Country Mountain Bike National Series (USXC) is back for 2025, bringing eight premier events nationwide. The series attracts top-tier talent and gives racers of all levels the chance to compete with some of the best in the nation. With UCI-sanctioned events, a pathway to national championships, and a mix of legendary and new venues, the 2025 season will be one of the most competitive yet.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley.png\"><img width=\"1152\" height=\"630\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series Trek Riley\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley.png 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley-297x162.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley-120x66.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-Trek-Riley-768x420.png 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos: USA Cycling)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>What is it?</strong> </em>The USA Cycling Cross-Country Mountain Bike National Series offers Olympic-style and short-track cross-country racing via eight prestigious events. The events on this calendar are UCI-sanctioned, allowing riders to earn UCI points.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Why does it matter?</em> </strong>The USXC Open Series is more than a race series; it’s a crucial stepping stone for riders climbing national and international rankings. For Junior racers, these events offer a direct ticket to the finals at the 2025 USA Cycling Cross-Country Mountain Bike National Championships. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021-.jpeg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021-.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/World-Cup-Snowshoe-Blevens-rolling-2021--768x576.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong>2025 USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series Calendar</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 1: Orange Seal Pro Cup p/b Velocity + UCI XCO Junior Series</strong>.</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Temecula, CA | <strong>March 7-9, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The series kicks off at Velocity Bike Park in Temecula, California. This purpose-built venue features fast and flowy short-track racing alongside cross-country battles for both UCI and amateur riders. Expect big talent and early-season fireworks.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC.png\"><img width=\"1160\" height=\"624\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series XC\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC.png 1160w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC-297x160.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC-120x65.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-XC-768x413.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 2: US Pro Cup + UCI XCO Junior Series</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Fayetteville, AR | <strong>March 19-22, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Centennial Park hosts round two, where the purpose-built World Cup-style course will test riders’ technical chops and endurance. With top-level competition and the scenic Ozarks backdrop, this stop is a must-watch.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge-.png\"><img width=\"1154\" height=\"628\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge-.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series anglers ridge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge-.png 1154w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge--297x162.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge--120x65.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-anglers-ridge--768x418.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 3: Showdown at Angler’s Ridge</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Danville, VA | <strong>April 11-13, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The only East Coast UCI race in 2025, this event features a tough but rewarding course designed to challenge both elite and amateur racers. Angler’s Ridge delivers a mix of fast descents and punchy climbs—bring your climbing legs!</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood-.png\"><img width=\"1150\" height=\"626\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood-.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series engelwood\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood-.png 1150w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood--297x162.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood--120x65.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-engelwood--768x418.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 4: Englewood Open p/b TREK + UCI XCO Junior Series</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Fall River, WI | <strong>May 2-4, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This UCI C1 event doubles as the WORS (Wisconsin Off Road Series) opener on the Englewood Grass Farm. A weekend of top-tier racing features a short track on Friday, the USXC round on Saturday, and a WORS showdown on Sunday.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel.png\"><img width=\"1154\" height=\"634\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series big wheel\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel.png 1154w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel-297x163.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel-120x66.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-big-wheel-768x422.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 5: Missoula XC – Griz Edition</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Missoula, MT | <strong>June 21-22, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Missoula’s legendary climbs and tight switchbacks are back for another year with a fresh “Griz Edition” theme. Saturday’s event is now part of the Junior World Series, and the Short Track XCC remains a fan favorite.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek.png\"><img width=\"1152\" height=\"632\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series trek\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek.png 1152w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek-297x163.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek-120x66.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-trek-768x421.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 6: Soho Bike Fest (Continental Series Event)</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Midway, UT | <strong>June 27-29, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The newly minted Soho Bike Fest is now part of the UCI Continental Series and one of five US Pro Cup circuit stops. Expect three days of racing, big crowds, and some of the best trail conditions in the West.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB-.png\"><img width=\"1148\" height=\"608\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB-.png\" alt=\"USA Cycling Cross-Country MTB National Series MTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB-.png 1148w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB--297x157.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB--120x64.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/USA-Cycling-Cross-Country-MTB-National-Series-MTB--768x407.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 7: ORA Trails Fest</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>La Crosse, WI | <strong>August 15-17, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Set against the stunning Mississippi River bluffs, ORA Trails Fest delivers a demanding mix of UCI XCO, XCC, Enduro, and XC racing. An actual all-around test, this event will push riders to their limits.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"2048\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Athletes compete in the UCI US Cup MTB XC cycling race held in Fayetteville, Arkansas, USA, April 12-15, 2023. (Photo by Bill Schieken/CXHAIRS Media)\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--297x238.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--1536x1229.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--120x96.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--768x614.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/CXHAIRS-Bill-Schieken-Podcast-MTB-XCO--2048x1639.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Athletes compete in the UCI US Cup MTB XC cycling race held in Fayetteville, Arkansas, USA, April 12-15, 2023. (Photo by Bill Schieken/CXHAIRS Media)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4><strong>Stop 8: UCI California MTB Triple</strong></h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Nevada City, CA | <strong>October 11-12, 2025</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The grand finale in California features UCI-sanctioned racing for Juniors, U23, and Elite XCO riders, along with amateur categories to round out the season. It’s a fitting capstone to a thrilling series.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With eight stops spanning coast to coast, the 2025 USXC Open Series is shaping to be an all-out battle for national greatness. Whether you’re looking to earn valuable UCI points, race against the best, or enjoy some world-class mountain biking, there’s a stop for you.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.uscupmtb.com/california-event\">Register for all events here </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/usa-cycling-xc-mtb-national-series-returns-for-2025/\">USA Cycling XC MTB National Series Returns for 2025</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"ec16bcd6ba04882bcfcbdcb3fa6d7f743fb21566118835d156747884de6ed6b2","category":"Cycling"}